                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.77/1492</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Reinsch</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-18T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 18, 1915, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Complaints received stating Hukuang asks bid for locomotives requiring British
                    design and that administration expects to place order by private tender contrary
                    to agreement concerning American standards and public opening of bids. Urge the
                    Minister of Communications to instruct as promised in your telegram of November
                    11, 1914.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
